///|
/// Exact result guidance for the evidence-analysis step. MoonClaw may reason
/// about the evidence, but it must return one candidate value that MoonBook can
/// validate deterministically; it never owns persistence or acceptance.
fn bookkeeper_three_gap_analyze_prompt() -> String {
  "Act as MoonBook Bookkeeper on MoonClaw for ${proposal.title}. Read the external packet, the exact Bookkeeper snapshot, and every canonical evidence reference before reasoning. This step applies only when subject_stage is exactly outcome_binding; otherwise return a completed not_applicable analysis without proposing a finding. For an outcome binding, select exactly one most evidence-supported gap class: information_gap (unknown_to_known), recognition_gap (known_to_matters), or decisiveness_gap (matters_to_act). Return exactly one moonbook.bookkeeper.moonclaw-result.v1 object with exactly these top-level keys: contract_version, packet_id, source_packet_digest, source_snapshot_digest, subject, subject_stage, evidence_refs, producer, model, candidate. Standard MoonClaw content must contain exactly one lowercase ```json fenced block containing only that canonical object, with no other fenced blocks. Copy packet_id, both source digests, subject, and subject_stage exactly from the packet; copy top-level and payload evidence_refs exactly from packet metadata.canonical_evidence_refs in its provided order. producer must be moonclaw and model must be gpt-5.6-sol. candidate must be one singular object, never an array, with exactly these keys: record_id, record_version, stage, title, summary, owner_route, recorded_at, links, issue_refs, next_action, payload. candidate.stage must be the lowercase value three_gap_finding. candidate.links must bind the exact outcome subject. payload must contain exactly: contract_version, candidate_schema, subject, learning_key, gap_class, transition, severity, owner_route, summary, evidence_refs, source_snapshot_digest, source_packet_digest. payload.summary must equal candidate.summary byte-for-byte. payload.owner_route must equal candidate.owner_route byte-for-byte. Copy payload.learning_key exactly from packet metadata.result_contract.learning_key; MoonClaw must never invent or alter it. payload.contract_version must be moonbook.bookkeeper.three_gap.v1 and payload.candidate_schema must be three_gap_finding.v1. The transition must match the one selected gap class, severity must be a single integer supported by the evidence, and both payload source digests must exactly repeat the top-level values. Do not emit three findings, a composite three-findings object, a findings array, candidates, per-gap subobjects, or more than one gap_class. Do not mutate .moonbook/bookkeeper, install authority, claim human acceptance, fabricate evidence or receipts, dispatch MoonCode, or apply a capability. MoonBook alone validates and durably records the candidate; a later named-human Bookkeeper review remains mandatory."
}

///|
/// Capability aggregation is irrelevant to an outcome-binding request, but it
/// must complete so the canonical Three-Gap handoff step can run. This does
/// not relax the promotion gate for accepted finding subjects.
fn bookkeeper_capability_aggregate_prompt() -> String {
  "Inspect subject_stage, the exact Bookkeeper snapshot, and the prior analysis for ${proposal.title}. If subject_stage is outcome_binding, return a completed result with applicability exactly not_applicable and reason exactly outcome_binding_requires_three_gap_handoff; preserve the prior single Three-Gap candidate unchanged for the next handoff step. Do not request input, return needs_input, wait for a persisted finding, or attempt capability aggregation in this branch. If subject_stage is three_gap_finding, aggregate a capability proposal only from Three-Gap finding records that already have exact named-human Accept receipts in the snapshot and satisfy the declared evidence and promotion policy. Never treat a finding drafted earlier in this same run as reviewed. When that promotion gate is not met, return a completed non_promotion result listing missing exact evidence or review links; do not request input and do not fabricate acceptance. Keep MoonCode work-order projection separate and non-executing. Do not persist, review, dispatch, or adopt any record."
}

///|
/// Serialize the derived candidate in the exact standard MoonClaw content
/// shape accepted by MoonBook's deterministic ingester.
fn bookkeeper_moonbook_handoff_prompt() -> String {
  "Package exactly one valid candidate as moonbook.bookkeeper.moonclaw-result.v1. Standard MoonClaw content must contain exactly one lowercase ```json fenced block containing only the canonical object, with no other fenced blocks. Copy packet_id, source_packet_digest, source_snapshot_digest, subject, subject_stage, and metadata.result_contract.learning_key exactly from the packet. Set producer to moonclaw and model to gpt-5.6-sol. The candidate object must contain exactly record_id, record_version, stage, title, summary, owner_route, recorded_at, links, issue_refs, next_action, and payload. payload.summary must equal candidate.summary byte-for-byte. payload.owner_route must equal candidate.owner_route byte-for-byte. For an outcome_binding, emit only a three_gap_finding.v1 payload linked exactly to the subject, use the packet-provided learning_key, and copy top-level and payload evidence_refs exactly from packet metadata.canonical_evidence_refs in its provided order; MoonClaw must never invent or reorder them. For a human-accepted three_gap_finding, emit capability_proposal.v1 only when at least two exact accepted source findings satisfy the promotion policy, and use the canonical evidence of all exact linked accepted findings. The payload must repeat the exact source digests and evidence; never invent evidence, authority, acceptance, receipts, or capability application. The next deterministic command is `moonbook bookkeeper moonclaw ingest-result <root> <packet.json> <result.json>`; named-human `moonbook bookkeeper review` remains later. Return no extra JSON fields and do not execute either mutation."
}
